 RAMASWAMI, V.
 GROVER, A.N.
 
CITATION: 1969 AIR 1122 1969 SCR (3) 708 1969 SCC (1) 671 
ACT:
 Income-tax Act, 1922, s. 33-Tribunal's powers--Tribunal cannot amalgamate income of two assessment years and divide it equally between them--Cannot take undertaking from assessee to file fresh return for earlier year and direct Income-tax Officer to make assessment accordingly-Cannot make allowance for 'intangible additions' without giving reasons.
 
